    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Porter</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 29, 1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No. 101
                    of the 9th instant, reporting that you had brought the case of Nicolino Mileo to
                    the attention of the Italian Government, which had promised a prompt and
                    thorough investigation of it.</p>
                <p>Awaiting your further reply upon this subject, and adding that the claimant’s
                    attorney has been advised of the presentation of the case and of the promise of
                    the Italian Government respecting it,</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William F. Wharton</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
